> For extra points, there's a fresh arugula salad on the side. Lunch in 10
> minutes doesn't get better than this!

Halve @flatbreads{2}(crosswise); toast in #9.5-10-inch stainless steel pan{}
until golden.

Wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice @tomato{1} into rounds; lightly season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

In a large #bowl{}, combine @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, a large drizzle of
@olive oil{2%tsp}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings). Add
@arugula{2%oz} and toss to combine; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Spread smooth sides of toasted flatbreads with @ricotta cheese{4%oz}. Top half
the flatbreads with @prosciutto{2%oz}, tomato slices, and as much salad as you
like. Top with remaining flatbreads, coated sides down.

Halve sandwiches crosswise. Divide between #plates{}; serve with any remaining
salad on the side.